result.name: High Tide restaurant

reviews.text: Good food, especially mango with sticky rice. Fair price,  only problem is busy all the time, and not very comfortable seat

Sumptuous food and delightful service - when I miss really excellent gourmet style home cooking (yes there is such a thing!) - then this is place on my list!
My favourite is the salmon either grilled or how the chef likes to make it perfectly - served with roasted vegetables that are fresh minutes before. combine this with a side of gratin style potatoes and you are in culinary heaven...but never forget the piece d la resitance: malva pudding with homemade ice cream... a serious meal not be rushed - enjoy the riverwalk area while enjoying great conversation!

We loved the Stoupe! Awesome freshly made bread with olive tapanade and hummus. The Greek salad has the best tasting tomatoes we've had in Hong Kong and the New Zealand lamb chop was superb. The Shiraz/ Cab is so good we bought a bottle to bring home. After a trek over the mountain from DB a tasty cold African IPA was delightful. But the owner is the best part of the place. Well done!
Excellent service and good location.  Mix of South African cuisine and some Thai.
Food is good and reasonably priced. Staff friendly. Lovely ambience

result.name: The STOEP at high tide

reviews.text: A nice restaurant to eat at if you're out this far. Most of the cuisine and drinks are based off South African favourites. Reasonably priced too.

This is the real thing on South Lantau !! 
If you come here to get away from the hustle and cranking pulse of the city then reward your self with a culinary holiday that is an inspiration to your palate and your spirit! 
Sumptuous food and delightful service - when I miss really excellent gourmet style home cooking (yes there is such a thing!) - then this is place on my list!
My favourite is the salmon either grilled or how the chef likes to make it perfectly - served with roasted vegetables that are fresh minutes before. combine this with a side of gratin style potatoes and you are in culinary heaven...but never forget the piece d la resitance: malva pudding with homemade ice cream... a serious meal not be rushed - enjoy the riverwalk area while enjoying great conversation!
Seriously the food is comfort plus taste! And the service comes with attention to the things that make sure you are never disappointed. 
Try the South African dishes! The are the best and after all ... You are getting out away from the city aren't you?
Clean bistro type place, good quality food and very friendly crew.

Good food.
Good service.
A good taste of home.
Nice food and service. Low price of lunch set comparing in this community.
